Sona is actually quite effective (at least as far as low Diamond) in wombo-combo comps or in games where teamfights are going to be more extended and less burst. You can check lolking, she has a reasonable pickrate and sits above a 52% winrate.

Zilean and Elise need help. Zilean has buffs inc already, and Riot is apparently trying to buff Elise, they just sorta failed thus-far.

Udyr is perfectly playable, even strong in the right circumstances. His major downfall is being played into heavy kite comps.


As of right now, its hard to find 5 champs that are bad enough to be considered unplayable. And most of those are either on the rework list or are champions Riot is showing an interest in improving. Yorrik is the only champion I can find that isn't due for a rework "soon" and Riot isn't looking into buffing.

